item.title: Need help! My server doesn't work
item.dc:creator: @p0wnag3ninja p0wnag3ninja
item.description:
@p0wnag3ninja wrote:

Oh god-.- Here : http://192.168.1.254 Then Game & Application Sharing Then Create a new game or application, Name : Moparscape or w/e u want. and manual entry of port maps. Then Port range 43594 to 43594 translate to 43594 Then add Then Click on Assign a game or application to a local network device . Now there is ABC another bittorrent client , Click on it Then press m button there is mopar , Click on it and now Device : USER DEFIND Put your default gateway : Open your run Then type cmd Then In black box type ipconfig. Now u see your default gateway Put it to that user defind and and then add…Now u opened your 43594… Its not that hard .=.=

item.title: Need help! My server doesn't work
item.dc:creator: @adam3d90s adam3d90s
item.description:
@adam3d90s wrote:

If you tell us the make of your router for example Netgear, or Linkys we might beable to help since we dont know what kind of router you have we need to tell you to go to www.portforward.com and find your router so you can open up Port 43594

the website for your router is normaly an ip address witch can be found buy going to Command Prompt and typing Ipconfig

it will tell you your ipaddress you can just try to type them in your web browser and see if that works…

If you dont know how to get to COmmand Prompt Click Start —> find the RUN button —> then type in CMD —> then Hit Enter

You can also google your router + port Fowarding to find out how

Hope this helps you,

Adam
